  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2648",
  "title": "[refinementList] sortBy doesn't factor in transformData",
  "body": "When adding a transformData function to a refinement list, it is not factored in when sorting the refinements. The bug is reproduced here: https://jsfiddle.net/9ej3v2t6/\r\n\r\n1. added a refinement list widget for genres.\r\n2. added transformData function that changes the label of one of the genres from \"Comedy\" to \"Humor\"\r\n3. added `sortBy:['name:asc']` and would expect the refinements to be sorted correctly but we get Action, **Humor**, Crime etc.\r\n\r\nThis problem can be circumvented by using a custom function for sortBy, something like this:\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\nsortBy: function(a,b){\r\n  const genres = {'Comedy':'Humor'};\r\n  var nameA = a.name.toUpperCase(); // ignore upper and lowercase\r\n  var nameB = b.name.toUpperCase(); // ignore upper and lowercase\r\n\r\n  if (genres.hasOwnProperty(a.name)) nameA = genres[a.name].toUpperCase();\r\n  if (genres.hasOwnProperty(b.name)) nameB = genres[b.name].toUpperCase();\r\n\r\n  if (nameA < nameB) {\r\n    return -1;\r\n  }\r\n  if (nameA > nameB) {\r\n    return 1;\r\n  }\r\n // names must be equal\r\n return 0;\r\n}\r\n```",
